  <brief_title>Changes of Parameters of Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation in Patients With Spinal Cord Injury</brief_title>
  <official_title>Reorganization of Cortical Motor Activation in Patients With Spinal Cord Injury: a Study of Motor Evoked Potential</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>National Taiwan University Hospital</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>National Taiwan University Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      CNS reorganization is evidenced in patients with CNS lesion, no exception to the patients
      with spinal cord injury. The paraplegics have to increase their loading of upper extremities
      to compesate the lost function of lower extremities. We hypothesize that CNS reorganization
      can happen in the chronic paraplegics. We try to compare the changes of parameters of
      transcranial magnetic stimulation in these patients with the normal population
      cross-sectionally.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
